<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FFD6FF9CA7ADFD17FBE6DA26" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0755A263FFD6FF9CA7ADFD17FEF0DF13" blockId="79.[189,310,760,786]" box="[189,310,760,786]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
<heading id="5C1D150FFFD6FF9CA7ADFD17FEF0DF13" bold="true" box="[189,310,760,786]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA7ADFD17FEF0DF13" bold="true" box="[189,310,760,786]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FFD6FF9CA7ADFCC6FD00D8DC" blockId="79.[188,1401,808,1246]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
Based on the description of 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FFD6FF9CA51DFCC6FC03DF42" author="Armas L. F. &amp; Palomino-Cardenas A. C. &amp; Castillo-Espinoza M." box="[525,965,808,835]" firstAuthor="Armas" journalOrPublisher="Revista Iberica de Aracnologia" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" pagination="45 - 50" part="28" refId="ref146496" refString="Armas L. F., Palomino-Cardenas A. C. &amp; Castillo-Espinoza M. d. 2016. Amblipigios de los Departamentos Cusco y Madre de Dios, Peru, con la descripcion de un nuevo Charinus (Amblypygi: Charinidae, Phrynidae). Revista Iberica de Aracnologia 28: 45 - 50." title="Amblipigios de los Departamentos Cusco y Madre de Dios, Peru, con la descripcion de un nuevo Charinus (Amblypygi: Charinidae, Phrynidae)" type="journal article" year="2016">Armas &amp; Palomino-Cárdenas (2016)</bibRefCitation>
, this species may be separated from other 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFD6FF9CA617FCA1FEB2DF69" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[263,372,846,872]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA617FCA1FEB2DF69" box="[263,372,846,872]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Charinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in western South America by means of the following combination of characters: carapace, chelicerae, pedipalps and opisthosomal tergites moderately dark, yellowish-brown; legs pale yellowish-brown; ocular tubercle black; carapace and pedipalps with clavate setae; median and lateral eyes well developed; basal segment of chelicera without tooth in retrolateral row; bifid tooth on basal segment with dorsal cusp larger than ventrodistal; cheliceral claw with five teeth; pedipalp femur with three dorsal spines, three ventral spines, and two setiferous tubercles proximal to first dorsal spine; pedipalp femur with spine proximal to first ventral spine of primary series; pedipalp patella with four dorsal spines and two ventral spines, and with long setiferous tubercle between spine I and distal margin; pedipalp tarsus with two dorsal spines; leg IV basitibia with three pseudo-articles; trichobothrium 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA24DFB96FABFD892" box="[1373,1401,1145,1171]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">bc</emphasis>
situated closer to 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA698FB71FE6CD8B9" box="[392,426,1182,1208]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">sbf</emphasis>
than to 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA516FB71FDDBD8B9" box="[518,541,1182,1208]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">bf</emphasis>
; leg IV distitibia 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA5F7FB70FD39D8B9" box="[743,767,1183,1208]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">sc</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA426FB71FC8CD8B9" box="[822,842,1182,1208]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">sf</emphasis>
series each with five trichobothria; tibia of leg I with 23 articles, tarsus I with 27–30 articles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FFD6FF9CA7ADFAE8FBE6DA26" blockId="79.[188,1400,1287,1575]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFD6FF9CA7ADFAE8FE70D920" authorityName="Armas &amp; Palomino-Cardenas" authorityYear="2016" box="[189,438,1287,1313]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longitarsus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA7ADFAE8FE70D920" box="[189,438,1287,1313]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Charinus longitarsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFD6FF9CA587FAE8FCA7D920" box="[663,865,1287,1313]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA587FAE8FCC2D920" box="[663,772,1287,1313]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Charinus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the combination of the long first article of the leg I tarsus, the clavate setae on the tegument, and sternites with plate-like platelets. These characters are otherwise present only in 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFD6FF9CA509FABDFD6AD96D" authority="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff, 2021" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" box="[537,684,1362,1388]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carvalhoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA509FABDFD6AD96D" box="[537,684,1362,1388]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">C. carvalhoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EADC30AFFD6FF9CA5A3FABDFCD7D96D" box="[691,785,1362,1388]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFD6FF9CA40DFABDFC0FD96D" authority="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff, 2021" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" box="[797,969,1362,1388]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magalhaesi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA40DFABDFC0FD96D" box="[797,969,1362,1388]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">C. magalhaesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EADC30AFFD6FF9CA4C0FABDFBEDD96D" box="[976,1067,1362,1388]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFD6FF9CA375FABDFB3FD96D" authorityName="Weygoldt" authorityYear="1972" box="[1125,1273,1362,1388]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA375FABDFB3FD96D" box="[1125,1273,1362,1388]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">C. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFD6FF9CA218FABDFEE9D990" authority="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff, 2021" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carvalhoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA218FABDFEE9D990" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Charinus carvalhoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EADC30AFFD6FF9CA628FA97FE52D993" box="[312,404,1400,1426]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFD6FF9CA6C1FA97FDAED990" authorityName="Weygoldt" authorityYear="1972" box="[465,616,1400,1426]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA6C1FA97FDAED990" box="[465,616,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">C. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be easily distinguished by the shape of the female gonopod, which is sucker-like, and the number of pseudo-articles in the basitibia of leg IV, three in 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFD6FF9CA3C0FA72FAB0D9B6" authorityName="Armas &amp; Palomino-Cardenas" authorityYear="2016" box="[1232,1398,1437,1463]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longitarsus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA3C0FA72FAB0D9B6" box="[1232,1398,1437,1463]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">C. longitarsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compared with four in 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFD6FF9CA6C0FA2DFDA0D9DD" authorityName="Weygoldt" authorityYear="1972" box="[464,614,1474,1500]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA6C0FA2DFDA0D9DD" box="[464,614,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">C. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and and two in 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFD6FF9CA438FA2DFC78D9DD" authority="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff, 2021" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" box="[808,958,1474,1500]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carvalhoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA438FA2DFC78D9DD" box="[808,958,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">C. carvalhoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EADC30AFFD6FF9CA4D5FA2CFBE7D9DC" box="[965,1057,1475,1501]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFD6FF9CA33AFA2DFAD4D9DD" authorityName="Weygoldt" authorityYear="1972" box="[1066,1298,1474,1500]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA33AFA2DFAD4D9DD" box="[1066,1298,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Charinus montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exhibits secondary sexual dimorphism, with the male pedipalps longer than those of the female, but sexual dimorphism is not mentioned in the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFD6FF9CA462F9E2FBDFDA26" authorityName="Armas &amp; Palomino-Cardenas" authorityYear="2016" box="[882,1049,1549,1575]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longitarsus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFD6FF9CA462F9E2FBDFDA26" box="[882,1049,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">C. longitarsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
